9. Third-Party Components

The Plugin may include or depend on third-party software components. Such
components are subject to their respective licenses, and You agree to comply
with those licenses. If there is a conflict between this EULA and a third-party
license with respect to a component, the third-party license will control for
that component. The Developer makes no warranties regarding third-party
components.

9.1. Third-Party Analytics Services

The Plugin and its website use third-party analytics services to improve the
product and prioritize development. The analytics are minimalistic and
privacy-conscious.

(a) PostHog (https://posthog.com). The Plugin uses PostHog as a server-side
analytics service. The Plugin may collect and send the following technical
event data:
- JetBrains IDE build, version, and product code;
- Plugin version;
- Anonymous project identifier (random UUID, not the project name); and
- exec_code call events (success/error).

No personally identifiable information is collected by this analytics feature.
You may opt out of Plugin analytics by disabling the
`mcp.steroid.analytics.enabled` registry key in the IDE.

(b) Cloudflare Web Analytics (https://www.cloudflare.com/web-analytics/).
The Plugin website at https://mcp-steroid.jonnyzzz.com uses Cloudflare Web
Analytics for privacy-first website traffic measurement. Cloudflare Web
Analytics does not use client-side state (such as cookies) and does not
track individuals across sites.

